<TITLE> Khaleda arrives in Barisal for rally </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 12 (bdnews24.com)  BNP chief Khaleda Zia arrived in Barisal on Wednesday afternoon to attend the divisional meeting. UPDATE Khaleda's motorcade reached Barisal at about 4pm. The opposition leader is scheduled to address the rally to be held at the city's Bells Park ground. The convoy of the BNP chief had left her cantonment house at around 9am. Party's standing committee member Sarwari Rahman is accompanying her, Khaleda's press secretary Maruf Kamal Khan said. This will be her first speech in the city since the Dec 29, 2008 national elections. Standing committee member Mirza Abbas, who has already arrived in Barisal, told bdnews24.com that all preparations were complete. This is the fourth of six grand rallies across the country. The first rally was held in Chittagong on Mar 29, the second one in Khulna on Apr 18 and the third held in Rajshahi on May 5. BNP will hold the next meeting in Dhaka on May 19 from where the opposition chief, as announced in Rajshahi rally, will declare anti-government movement programmes. The last of the divisional grand rallies will be held in Sylhet. bdnew
